We use a map to store the start times of the events. We iterate through the start times and check if the current time (i) is present in the map. If it is, we increment k. The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate through the start times once. The space complexity is O(n) because we use a map to store the start times. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a constant number of operations per iteration, and the map has a constant time complexity for lookup operations.

